{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TDv6G1jAnsV7p1YE2h944o","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so there are PVCs with ES 7.x data. I need to:\n1. Delete the StatefulSet (pods will be deleted automatically)\n2. Delete the PVCs (so ES 8.x starts fresh)\n3. Create TLS secrets and password secret\n4. Recreate everything for ES 8.11.1\n\nLet me proceed step by step.\n\nFirst, let me generate the TLS certificate. I'll create a CA and a server certificate with proper SANs.\n\nFor the certificate, I need SANs for:\n- `es-http` (the HTTP service)\n- `es-cluster` (the headless service)  \n- The individual pod FQDNs across the cluster\n- `localhost` and 127.0.0.1\n\nI'll use a single cert for both HTTP and transport TLS with certificate verification mode for transport. Now I'm writing the bash commands to generate the TLS cert, create the secrets, delete the old resources, and set up the new ones.\n\nWriting TLS generation and secret creation... I need to generate the certificates for transport TLS with proper key usage extensions and SANs for all nodes, then configure ES with `verification_mode: certificate` so it validates the cert chain without requiring hostname matching. I'm also realizing that upgrading from ES 7.x to 8.x with existing persistent volumes will fail, so I should delete the PVCs first to start with a clean slate.\n\nFor the StatefulSet migration, I'll delete it first (which preserves PVCs by default), then manually delete the PVCs, and recreate everything fresh. Regarding `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, I need to include it in the initial bootstrap configuration to form the cluster, though it's technically only required for first-time setup.\n\nSince we're deleting the PVCs and starting fresh, it's safe to keep this setting in the config. I also need to handle the `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` environment variable properly—in ES 8.x, this sets the initial password for the built-in `elast